I am here describing plot_plusminus_hprc.R

At the moment (2:51 PM) the script takes as inputs:


- (1) paf (more on that later)
- (2) SD.bed
- (3) genes.bed
- (4) chunklen of paf

And some hardcoded values: 
- (5) limit: 20
- (6) chrx_startcoord what we have to add to x to get the SD.bed and genes.bed numbers (they are in real coordinates)

The script then creates one of those plots as in example.png

Now for the different input files: 


(1) paf:
(1.1) Know your input coordinates. I got them with nahrwhals, and then e.g.: 

